The paper deals with the computational complexity of a graph exploration problem, which is a fundamental problem in computer science and falls under the category of algorithms and data structures (cs.DS). The problem also involves temporal graphs, which are commonly studied in the fields of artificial intelligence (cs.AI) and computational geometry (cs.CG). Additionally, the problem involves connectivity constraints, which are relevant in the field of social networks and network science (cs.SI). Finally, the paper uses techniques from complexity theory and graph theory, which are also relevant in the field of machine learning (cs.LG).
